      <!-- ── Deploy ── -->
      <section id="deploy">
        <h2>Self-Hosting — Deployment</h2>
        <p>ForgeLite is a single Node.js process. Recommended production setup:</p>

        <h3>System requirements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Node.js 22 or later</li>
          <li>Git 2.x</li>
          <li>~100 MB RAM minimum</li>
          <li>Disk space proportional to your repositories</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Production start</h3>
        <pre><code># Build TypeScript
npm run build

# Start with environment variables
PORT=3000 \
JWT_SECRET="$(openssl rand -hex 32)" \
DATA_DIR=/var/lib/forgelite \
BASE_URL=https://git.yourdomain.com \
node dist/server.js</code></pre>

        <h3>systemd service</h3>
        <pre><code># /etc/systemd/system/forgelite.service
[Unit]
Description=ForgeLite Git Hosting
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=forgelite
WorkingDirectory=/opt/forgelite
ExecStart=/usr/bin/node dist/server.js
Restart=always
Environment=PORT=3000
Environment=JWT_SECRET=your-secret-here
Environment=DATA_DIR=/var/lib/forgelite
Environment=BASE_URL=https://git.yourdomain.com

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target</code></pre>
        <pre><code>systemctl enable --now forgelite</code></pre>

        <h3>Data directory</h3>
        <p>All data is stored in <code>DATA_DIR</code>:</p>
        <pre><code>/var/lib/forgelite/
  forgelite.db          # SQLite database (users, repos, issues, PRs)
  repos/
    alice/
      my-project.git/   # Bare git repository
    bob/
      another-repo.git/</code></pre>
        <p>Back up the entire <code>DATA_DIR</code> to preserve everything.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- ── Nginx ── -->
      <section id="nginx">
        <h2>Self-Hosting — Nginx Reverse Proxy</h2>
        <p>Run Nginx in front of ForgeLite for SSL termination and efficient static file serving.</p>

        <pre><code># /etc/nginx/sites-available/forgelite
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name git.yourdomain.com;
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}

server {
    listen 443 ssl http2;
    server_name git.yourdomain.com;

    ssl_certificate     /etc/letsencrypt/live/git.yourdomain.com/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/git.yourdomain.com/privkey.pem;

    # Increase body size for git push of large repos
    client_max_body_size 100m;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;

        # Required for git smart HTTP protocol
        proxy_buffering off;
        proxy_request_buffering off;
    }
}</code></pre>

